\b - Experimental Set-up -\

\b0 Flies were introduced to the three tile arena and allowed to explore for 60 seconds with all tiles at 22\'b0C. After that the middle tile remained comfortable and the side tiles were heated to 34\'b0C. This created a pole position (PP) phase and lasted 60 seconds. After the PP a trial phase started and lasted another 60 seconds. The trial phase consisted of a side tile and the middle tile heating up to 40\'b0C and a side tile remaining safe at 22\'b0C. The safe side tile that was safe was indicated by a red LED light on at the start of the trial phase and  lasting the whole phase corresponding to the safe location (LED1 or the left one if the left tile was safe or LED2 or the right one if the right tile was safe).\
\
Each experiment consisted of 60 phases: 30 PP followed by 30 trials. The whole process was video recorded. The auditory stimulus was dependent on the condition the fly was in. Each tone was played at the beginning of the trial phase and was included in the 60 seconds the trial phase lasted.\

