\b - Conditions -\
\

\b0 All conditions 
\b N=20
\b0 .
\b \
\
TT
\b0 : A short and a long stimulus was presented. The short stimulus consisted of a tone of 300ms and had the left side as the safe location during the trial phase. The left red LED (LED1) turned on at the same time as the tone started. The long stimulus consisted of a tone of 900ms and had the right side as the safe location. The right red LED (LED2) turned on.\
\

\b OT
\b0 : The same stimulus of 600ms indicated left or right safe location. The left red LED turned on in case this was the safe tile and the right red LED turned on in case this was the safe location.\
\

\b NT
\b0 : This condition had no stimulus. Nevertheless, the left red LED turned on when the fly was supposed to the go the left and the right red LED turned on in case this was the correct side. The same script used to coordinate the OT experiments was used, except that no tone was played.
\b \

\b0 \
All tones were played at 400Hz and 80dB.\

